title: Lee crushes Jackson in city's oldest annual rivalry
text:
Lee crushes Jackson in city's oldest annual rivalry 
Sat, Oct 24, 2015 @ 12:20 am 
The Times-Union 
LEE 41 
JACKSON 14 
Tony Belle rushed for 169 yards and a TD on 18 carries and the Generals crushed the Tigers (0-8). ... QB Derrick Jones threw a pair of TD passes to Tyrique Thomas and rushed for a 2-yard score. Lee (5-3) remains in contention for a district runner-up spot in 2-7A. It hosts Fletcher next week.
